      "writtenOn": "2026-07-14T16:05:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "yes; CUE_REGISTRY in its simplest form is like GOPROXY, just a list of registries, but it also supports a key-value form where you can route different module prefixes to different modules. this is akin to Go\u0027s GOPRIVATE in a way, but much more powerful.\n\nSee `cue help registryconfig`, which has examples like:\n\n\u003e CUE_REGISTRY\u003d\u0027foo.example/bar\u003dlocalhost:5000,myregistry.example\u0027\n\nMost users won\u0027t need this, but this is very relevant for enterprise users where they want to use the central registry for OSS deps, but their on-premise registry for corporate code.",
      "parentUuid": "6ec84393_9b34f50d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 17,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 17,
        "endChar": 34
      },
